        "message": "LU-13643 mdt: implement workqueue for FLR state transitions\n\nThis patch implements a workqueue-based solution for handling\nFLR (File Level Replication) state transitions from WRITE_PENDING\nto RDONLY when the last active writer lock is released.\n\nThe workqueue approach solves the problem of performing FLR state\ntransitions in contexts where proper transaction environments\nmay not be available, such as during lock cancellation in\nblocking AST callbacks.\n\nKey changes:\n- Add mdt_flr_wq workqueue to mdt_device structure\n- Implement mdt_flr_queue_rdonly_transition() to queue work items\n- Implement mdt_flr_rdonly_work_fn() as the work function\n- Initialize workqueue during MDT startup in mdt_init0()\n- Cleanup workqueue during MDT shutdown in mdt_fini()\n- Update mdt_active_writer_dec() to use workqueue when no proper\n  environment is available\n\nThe workqueue ensures that FLR state transitions are performed\nin a proper thread context with appropriate transaction handling,\navoiding potential deadlocks and environment issues that can\noccur when called from blocking AST contexts.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d2e3f4a5b6c7d8e9f0a1b\n"
      },
